d", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 6, "created_at": "2020-02-13T12:59:47Z", "updated_at": "2020-02-20T08:57:18Z", "closed_at": "2020-02-20T08:57:18Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "It will perform a `rm -rf` on the remote end. No check if it would wipe out the last existing copy of a file, or whether there even is a dataset sibling.\r\n\r\nI propose the complete removal of this functionality. It is totally unexpected that a command that is called `create...` destroys something remote:\r\n\r\n```\r\n/tmp % mkdir precious\r\n/tmp % echo \"all my secret keys\" > precious/keys\r\n/tmp % datalad create reckless\r\n/tmp % cd reckless\r\n/tmp/reckless (git)-[master] % datalad create-sibling localhost:/tmp/precious\r\n[ERROR  ] Target path /tmp/precious already exists. And it fails to rmdir (rmdir: failed to remove '/tmp/precious': Directory not empty). [create_sibling.py:_create_dataset_sibling:161] (RuntimeError) \r\n\r\n# death\r\n/tmp/reckless (git)-[master] % datalad create-sibling localhost:/tmp/precious --existing replace\r\ncreate_sibling(ok): . (dataset)\r\n% ls -l /tmp/precious\r\ntotal 0\r\n\r\n```", "closed_by": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/events{/privacy}", "receive